{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3502043,"name":"Nicollas Ribeiro Luz","username":"NicollasLuz","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/59ef9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-04T19:28:30.172Z","cooked":"<p>I’m having trouble reading MegaTag2 with Limelight. Our Limelight identifies MegaTag2 and gives a very different position than the real one. For example, we went to read AprilTag 7 and the position the robot was in was the equivalent of AprilTag 10, that is, it was inverted. We also tried to read AprilTag 1 with the robot on the left side of the arena and it showed that the robot was on the right side. We tried to invert the Yaw of the Limelight on the web and we managed to fix the position on AprilTag 7. It showed the correct side, but when we read AprilTag 1, the robot went to the outside of the arena, showing itself on the opposite side of AprilTag. Does anyone know how to solve this? Do we have to save some web configuration in the <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span> or do we have to do something in the code? One addition is that MegaTag 1 was working normally, the position was just shaking a lot, as is usual with MegaTag1. Thank you all in advance.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-02-04T19:28:30.172Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":151,"reads":213,"readers_count":212,"score":797.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":485168,"topic_slug":"limelight-having-trouble-reading-megatag2","display_username":"Nicollas Ribeiro Luz","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staf