<p>How can I know what angle this is?</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":15,"updated_at":"2025-02-05T22:13:35.537Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":121,"readers_count":120,"score":54.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":485168,"topic_slug":"limelight-having-trouble-reading-megatag2","display_username":"Nicollas Ribeiro Luz","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":67020,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/limelight-having-trouble-reading-megatag2/485168/8","custom_user_title":"Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3503512,"name":"Jackson Elia","username":"Traptricker","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-05T23:05:33.985Z","cooked":"<p>Okay so your code should be something like this</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">LimelightHelpers.SetRobotOrientation("limelight", gyroAngle, gyroAngleRateOfChange,0,0,0,0);
</code></pre>
<p>You need to get the that your robot is currently facing from your gyro and the rate of change of the angle from the gyro, and then use those.</p>
<p>Do you have a navx:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">private final AHRS gyro = new AHRS(NavXComType.kMXP_SPI, NavXUpdateRate.k200Hz);

// Then in your drive subsystem periodic or something
@override
public void periodic() {
  LimelightHelpers.SetRobotOrientation("limelight", -gyro.getAngle(), -gyro.getRate(), 0, 0, 0, 0);
}
</code></pre>
<p>(navx has the angle as clockwise positive, hence doing the negative sign)</p>
